  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Making artisanal cobalt mining work for women and communities_Grand Katanga</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will focus on supporting the gender -responsive formalization of Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC) artisanal cobalt sector.  We will do this by increasing the capacities of women and men engaged in artisanal cobalt mining to comply with the new mining Code while ensuring women&apos;s rights are protected in the overall formalization effort.  This will include strengthening the influencing capacities of artisanal cooperatives, as well as improving their abilities to comply with environmental and occupational health and safety requirements.    Specifically, the project includes three principal objectives:  1. Build capacity and support for women&apos;s rights organizations (&quot;WROs&quot;) and women&apos;s associations to advocate for the effective implementation of provisions of the new mining code relating to the formalization of the artisanal mining sector, including the environmental protections and occupational health and safety requirements.  This will specifically include educating men and women working in Artisanal Mining (ASM) about women&apos;s rights and their legal protections.   2. Enhance capacity for three women&apos;s cooperatives in the formal registration process, including assisting them to obtain their artisanal miner license cards, as well as broader women&apos;s leadership skills and capacities necessary to support the enabling environments at the household, community, institutional, and political levels for women&apos;s engagement in ASM.   3. Empower women&apos;s cooperatives and civil society with lessons learned from project engagement, enabling these actors to effectively push ASM cooperatives, relevant DRC governmental authorities, and companies along the cobalt supply chain to improve practice or adopt reforms that better benefit ASM communities and the women involved in ASM.</narrative>
  </description>
